        align:Mapping ;
    prov:wasAttributedTo align:LLMAlignmentBot ;
    prov:wasGeneratedBy align:e58a2db1-5c28-40a2-a8b6-e77aaa929771 ;
    align:confidence "0.85"^^xsd:float ;
    align:rationale "The AIDOC concept describes the general activity of data validation for AI models. The vair concept 'Incomplete Validation Data' specifically identifies *a type* of problem within that broader validation process – namely, a lack of completeness in the dataset used for validation. Therefore, incomplete validation data is a specific case *of* data validation."^^xsd:string ;
    align:relation skos:narrowMatch ;
    align:source aidoc:DataValidation ;
    align:target <https://w3id.org/vair#IncompleteValidationData> .

align:a392890c-169b-4c18-a39f-fee35033cdb6 a prov:Entity,
        align:Mapping ;
    prov:wasAttributedTo align:LLMAlignmentBot ;
    prov:wasGeneratedBy align:e58a2db1-5c28-40a2-a8b6-e77aaa929771 ;
    align:confidence "0.85"^^xsd:float ;
    align:rationale "Both concepts relate to monitoring after deployment. However, 'Post-market Monitoring Plan' (vair) explicitly references the AI Act and implies a *plan* – a documented approach. 'Post-market Monitoring Activity' (AIDOC) is the execution of that plan or general monitoring. They are highly related and could be used interchangeably in many contexts, but aren’t identical."^^xsd:string ;
    align:relation skos:closeMatch ;
    align:source aidoc:PostMarketMonitoringActivity ;
    align:target <https://w3id.org/vair#PostMarketMonitoringPlan> .

